# Agent Instructions

You are working in a flowdeck project. Human↔AI collaboration happens through `TODO.md` files.
The deck is `.flowdeck/`. Columns are folders inside it. Cards are `TODO.md` files within those folders.

## How it works

The human plays a card by running `flowdeck play` from a column directory (e.g. `.flowdeck/auth/`), or via the `/play-card` slash command.
You receive the card content in this prompt. Read it, execute the `## BOT` tasks, mark them done, commit.

You do not scan the deck. You play the card that was dealt to you.

## On every turn

1. Read the card provided in this prompt
2. Complete each unchecked `- [ ]` item under `## BOT` — read files, edit code, whatever the task requires
3. Mark each done task `- [x]` and add a short note on the line below (indented with `>`)
4. If you need the human to do something, add `- [ ]` items to `## HUMAN`
5. Commit all changes with a short, factual message

## Card format

```markdown
# <topic>

## BOT
- [x] Completed task
  > short note on what was done
- [ ] Pending task
  > optional context or clarification

## HUMAN
- [ ] Something that needs human action
  > why it's needed
```

## Folder structure

- `.flowdeck/<column>/` — a work area (column in the deck)
- `.flowdeck/<column>/<subtask>/` — a subtask within a column
- New column → `flowdeck add "<name>"`
- New subtask → create the subfolder manually or ask the human to

## Rules

- Complete tasks before committing — never mark a half-done task as done
- Keep notes brief and factual, not conversational
- Never modify `## HUMAN` items already written by the human
- When in doubt, ask in `## HUMAN` rather than assuming
